    "body": "This PR improves TileLang's `cp.async` support and frontend async-copy semantics.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- Add CPAsync as a `Copy` instruction and lower eligible global->shared vectorized copies to `ptx_cp_async`.\r\n- Introduce `T.async_copy` / `tl.tileop.async_copy` with explicit async semantics (emits `cp.async` + `commit`, but does not auto-insert `wait`).\r\n- Keep `T.copy` synchronous semantics: when it lowers to `cp.async`, it auto-emits `commit` + `wait<0>` to preserve correctness.\r\n- Rename `SimplifyCPAsyncSync` to `OptimizeCPAsyncSync` (keeps a backward-compatible alias).\r\n- Teach `ThreadSync(\"shared\")` to treat `ptx_cp_async` writes as async-copy writes, avoiding unnecessary `__syncthreads()` between back-to-back `cp.async` stages.\r\n- Docs: clarify `T.copy` vs `T.async_copy` semantics and synchronization expectations.\r\n\r\nTesting:\r\n- `pytest -q testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_access_ptr_codegen.py testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_pipeline_planning.py testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_Inject_software_pipeline.py`\r\n- `python debug/gemm_example.py`\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Exposed async_copy (T.async_copy) API and added OptimizeCPAsyncSync transform.\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * cp.async-aware lowering, vectorization, and scheduling for async-copy patterns.\n  * Pipeline planning and thread-storage sync now model cp.async groups, commits, and waits.\n  * Manual pipeline handling simplified and supported for explicit pipeline annotations.\n  * Improved codegen equivalence and synchronization behavior for async copies.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added end-to-end tests for async-copy codegen, cp.async sync optimizations, and pipeline planning.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Documented T.async_copy semantics and comparison with T.copy.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
